-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Subject: Git Configurations
From: Robert Buck
Date: 2011-07-19

Contents:

Several configuration setters for Git are provided in this directory:

  set-gitignore-core.sh     - configures the global .gitignore file to ignore
                              default patterns encountered

  set-gitignore-eclipse.sh  - configures the global .gitignore file to ignore
                              common eclipse files

  set-gitignore-java.sh     - configures the global .gitignore file to ignore
                              common java files

  set-gitignore-maven.sh    - configures the global .gitignore file to ignore
                              common maven files

  set-gitignore-vstudio.sh  - configures the global .gitignore file to ignore
                              visual studio files; for illustrative purposes
                              only

Java developers are strongly encouraged to run these set-gitignore-* scripts.
